                <td width="55" height="21" align="center">31</td>
				<td valign="bottom"><img src="/english/images/bbs_line.gif"></td>
                <td align="left" style="padding:5 10" width="388"><font class="title01">Pantech to Drive Global Expansion With Launch of Distinctive “Slim-Series”</font> </td>
				<td valign="bottom"><img src="/english/images/bbs_line.gif"></td>
                <td width="100" align="center">Sep.08,2005</td>
              </tr>
			  <tr class="bbs05"> 
                <td height="1" colspan="5"><img src="/english/images/blank.gif"></td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bbs03"> 
                <td colspan="2" height="21" align="center">&nbsp;</td>
                <td colspan="3" align="left" style="padding:5 10">SEOUL, September 8th, 2005 - Pantech, one of the world’s leading mobile communications groups - comprised of Pantech&Curitel Communications, Inc., Pantech Co. and Pantech C&I Inc. (“Pantech” hereafter) - today unveiled its premium “Slim-Series” of handsets, as the latest stage in the ongoing expansion of its global scope of operations.<br>
<br>
The Slim-Series, which will initially be launched in Russia and subsequently in other global markets, is composed of the PG-1400, PG-1500, PG-3500 and PG-3600 models and is the ideal choice for trend conscious consumers who are looking for a stylish yet slim and durable handset, with an exceptional range of applications.<br>
<br>
Sung-Kyu Lee, President & CEO, Pantech Co., said: “For Pantech, the Slim-Series represents a major step forward in mobile technology and design innovation, as the handsets have been built to incorporate essential multi-functional applications and features, without compromising on super slim exteriors and lightweight durability”.<br>
<br>
“We feel that this combination marks the Slim-Series handsets out as something different in the mobile phone sector. These handsets are perfectly suited to stylish people, who are looking for phones that provide sophisticated yet user friendly features to compliment their lifestyles,” said Mr. Lee.<br>
<br>
Pantech is focused on further expanding its premium image in key markets, such as Russia, where it dominates the high-tier handset sector with 8% market share. As part of the growth of the Pantech brand name, Pantech plans to ramp up its sales and marketing presence across Europe, South America, China, India, and the Middle East over the coming months.<br>
<br>
The PG-1500 handset is a light, yet stylishly designed, GSM tri-band clamshell phone, which features a wide 1.8 inch 65K color LCD screen and a 64 polyphonic ringtone and MP3 ringtone. Likewise, the clamshell PG-3500 phone and the PG-3600, a slider model, both feature a diverse range of functions within a slim handset, typifying the emphasis of the Slim-Series on ensuring optimal functionality within a compact frame. <br>
<br>
<br>
***more***<br>
<br>
<br>
Both the PG-3500 and PG-3600 phones include a 1.3 Mega Pixels CMOS Camera, MPEG 4 camcorder, and MP3 player supported by external memory, as well as Bluetooth/USB and WAP 2.0/JAVA technology, and 64 polyphonic ring tones.<br>
  <br>
PG-1500 features include:<br>
l	Intenna Clamshell<br>
l	Thickness 14.8 mm<br>
l	Weight 75g<br>
l	Main LCD 1.8” 65K CSTN<br>
l	64 polyphonic ringtone/ MP3 ringtone<br>
l	UM(SMS,EMS,MMS)<br>
l	WAP2.0/JAVA<br>
<br>
PG-3500 features include:<br>
l	Intenna Clamshell with dual color LCD<br>
l	Thickness 15.8 mm<br>
l	Weight 75g<br>
l	Main LCD 1.9” 260K TFT<br>
l	Sub LCD 1.2” 65K TFT<br>
l	1.3 Mega Pixels CMOS Camera<br>
l	64 polyphonic/MP3 ring tone<br>
l	UM(SMS, EMS, MMS), IM. E-mail client<br>
l	WAP 2.0/JAVA<br>
l	Bluetooth/USB<br>
<br>
PG-3600 features include:<br>
l	Intenna Slider<br>
l	Thickness 16.8 mm<br>
l	Weight 75g<br>
l	Main LCD 1.9” 260K TFT<br>
l	1.3 Mega Pixels CMOS Camera<br>
l	64 polyphonic/MP3 ring tone<br>
l	UM(SMS, EMS. MMS), IM, E-mail client<br>
l	WAP 2.0/JAVA<br>
l	Bluetooth/USB<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
***more***<br>
<br>
<br>
Availability: <br>
The T-Series of handsets will become available in Russia from next month and in other markets subsequently.<br>
<br>
About Pantech:<br>
Pantech, through its affiliates - Pantech Co., Ltd., Pantech&Curitel Communications, Inc. and Pantech C&I Inc - is ranked second in the South Korean domestic market and marked as the seventh largest mobile handset manufacturer in the world. Pantech is also recognized as one of the world’s fastest growing providers of mobile communications solutions. Pantech has been responsible for a number of breakthrough innovations in the mobile technology sector, including the introduction in 2004 of the world’s first fingerprint recognition camera phone, as well as award winning camcorder and MP3 phones. In May 2005, Pantech affiliate Pantech&Curitel Communications, Inc. announced the acquisition of SK Teletech Co., Ltd., the fourth largest handset manufacturer in the Korean market. SK Teletech was originally the handset manufacturing arm of SK Telecom, number one mobile network operator in Korea. Under the terms of the acquisition agreement, Pantech and SK Telecom plan to collaborate in joint research and development initiatives and will work together in the global expansion of their respective businesses into overseas markets, The SKY brand, marketed by SK Teletech, is the most popular premium handset brand in Korea. In August 2005, to facilitate the goal of Pantech becoming one of the world’s top five mobile handset brands, the Pantech Co. and SK Teletech were merged under the Pantech organization. Pantech collectively has more than 5,000 employees and a total of 20 regional sales offices worldwide. Pantech - through its affiliates - reported total revenues of approximately US$4 billion in 2004. For more information on Pantech, please visit: www.pantech.com or www.curitel.com.<br>
